                {
                    "title": "<span style=\"font-size:26px;\"> </span>",
                    "content": "\n<div class=\"methodology\">\n<h1 class=\"methodology-subtitle\">About the data</h1>\n<div class=\"methodology-definitions\">\n<h2>Definitions</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<span class=\"concept\">Child marriage</span>: <span class=\"definition\">Proportion of women aged 20\u201424 who were married or in a union before age 15 and before age 18. It is calculated by dividing the number of women aged 20\u201424 who were first married or in a union by age 15 or age 18 by the total number of women aged 20\u201424 in the population. </span>\n</li>\n<li>\n<span class=\"concept\">xxx</span>: <span class=\"definition\">xxx</span>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div class=\"methodology-coverage\">\n<h2>Coverage</h2>\n<p>The indicator covers the proportion of women aged 20\u201424 who were first married or in a union by age 15 and by age 18.  Information is presented at the national level.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n",
